Maintainer: Alexander Henzi <henzi.alexander@gmail.com>
Description: Isotonic distributional regression (IDR) is a powerful
    nonparametric technique for the estimation of distributions of a binary or 
    numeric response variable conditional on numeric or ordinal covariates. IDR 
    assumes that there is a monotone relationship between the response 
    variable and the covariates, where the partial order on the covariate space
    can be specified by the user, and has no tuning parameters. It can be used
    to generate calibrated probabilistic weather forecasts from ensemble
    forecasts and observations, and serve as a benchmark in many other
    prediction problems.
